    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-12-30T09:50:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-12-30T09:50:00-05:00" n="676"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/322: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kreeck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-30T11:00:00-03:50"
                            >December 30, 1928—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 31—10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>44. Paraguay has telegraphed authorization to its representative in Washington to
                    sign the protocol in view of the threatening Bolivian advances although it is
                    confident that the investigation of recent events will not permit conciliation
                    and lasting peace. It feels that the Conference has taken the responsibility for
                    the cause. Until the entire question is determined, which Argentine mediation
                    will not do, Paraguay will be insecure and continuous peace defeated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kreeck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
